<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-11-13T13:36:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-11-13T13:36:00-05:00" n="1208" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1208">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/5482.</note>
                        <head ana="#head_untitled-inferred-from-preceding-sibling-head">[Untitled]</head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Embassy</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Mexico</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-11-13T12:00:00-06:36">
                                    <hi rend="italic">November 13, 1912—12
                                noon</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Rebels now control entire coast of Guerrero, most of Michoacán and the
                            State of Mexico, and are increasing in northern Chiapas.</p>
                        <p>Many political arrests and domiciliary visits by the police are being
                            made.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Schuyler.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>